main event: A sighting of an unusual aerial object was reported by a housewife in Blackburn, Melbourne on January 3, 1954.
interesting points: The object was described as silver and highly reflective,The sighting lasted for about 45 seconds,There was no visible trail or exhaust from the object,The witness was nervous and had no previous interest in UFOs,The sighting occurred in the vicinity of the sun and may have been a reflection.
